🧠 What is HTTP Module?

Node.js provides a built-in **http module** to:

✔ Create web servers
✔ Handle requests
✔ Send responses

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Basic HTTP Server

```javascript
const http = require("http");

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.write("Hello from HTTP server");
  res.end();
});

server.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Server running on port 3000");
});
```

📌 Visit: `http://localhost:3000`

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Handling Routes (Manual Way)

```javascript
const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {

  if (req.url === "/") {
    res.write("Home Page");
  } 
  else if (req.url === "/about") {
    res.write("About Page");
  } 
  else {
    res.write("404 Not Found");
  }

  res.end();
});
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

⚠️ Problems with HTTP Module

❌ Manual routing
❌ Complex code
❌ No middleware
❌ Hard to scale

👉 Solution → **Express.js**

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🚀 What is Express.js?

**Express.js** is a **Node.js framework** that simplifies backend development.

✔ Easy routing
✔ Middleware support
✔ Clean code
✔ Faster development

---

🔷 Install Express

```bash
npm install express
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Basic Express Server

```javascript
const express = require("express");

const app = express();

app.get("/", (req, res) => {
  res.send("Hello from Express");
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log("Server running on port 3000");
});
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Routing in Express

```javascript
app.get("/", (req, res) => {
  res.send("Home Page");
});

app.get("/about", (req, res) => {
  res.send("About Page");
});

app.get("/contact", (req, res) => {
  res.send("Contact Page");
});
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Handling JSON Response

```javascript
app.get("/api/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json([
    { id: 1, name: "John" },
    { id: 2, name: "Sara" }
  ]);
});
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Middleware (Very Important ⭐)

Middleware is a function that runs between request & response.

```javascript
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log("Request received");
  next();
});
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Built-in Middleware

```javascript
app.use(express.json());
```

✔ Parses JSON data

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Handling POST Request

```javascript
app.post("/api/data", (req, res) => {
  const data = req.body;
  res.send("Data received");
});
```

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Express vs HTTP Module

| Feature     | HTTP Module | Express  |
| ----------- | ----------- | -------- |
| Setup       | Complex     | Easy     |
| Routing     | Manual      | Built-in |
| Middleware  | No          | Yes      |
| Code Length | Long        | Short    |

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Example REST API

```javascript
const express = require("express");
const app = express();

app.use(express.json());

app.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json([{ id: 1, name: "John" }]);
});

app.post("/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json({ message: "User added" });
});

app.listen(3000);
```

